<br>
And you think this isn't the case already? Legends? Actually, even expansions. LoE getting you on EQ2 beta, etc. They do that wherever they think they can get away with it. I wouldn't put it past them to implement something like what Robin suggested. Especially if that experimental game works out. <br>
<br>
As for legal issues, I think it's arguable that even today items/chars have monetary value. <br>
<br>
True, the EULA forbids it, but I'm not positive it actually covers Sony, as the auction sites obviously exist, and SOE isn't doing much about it. By their neglect they might be considered to be condoning it... I'm not a lawyer, so I'm not positive about it, but I do know it is that way with copyright law; If you don't actively pursue infringements you lose the protection of the law. Either way, I don't think most of us want to go sue SOE over the loss of a quest item or a drop due to a bug or a server roll back, so I guess we'll never actually find out. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95331" target="_new">
<img border=0 src="http://www.tshrew.net/saga/bippin/BippinSig-5.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bippinfv>bippinfv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf-hugger</span><br>  Posts: 1921<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/03 10:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4630.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_money.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A Modest Proposal</span><hr size=1> Oh, and Greylight linkes to the Swift essay first  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/dot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 2229<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/03 10:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4630.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/smile.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_money.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Heh.</span><hr size=1> Swift's essay is indeed a fine and impressive work of irony.  He proposed the most gross thing he could to wake up the British landowners and other such in Britian to a very real problem with the poverty (and that is poverty below what we consider poverty today) in Ireland.  This was during the time of the potato famine when the deaths were soaring into thousands or even millions, people perishing for lack of -any- food while the landlords (British) were denying there was even any problem at all.  <br>
<br>
How does this relate to EQ?  It doesn't.  EQ is an entertainment, not a necessity of life (though entertainment is now viewed in society as being somewhat necessary).  SOE has acknowledged there is a problem, if only with tacit rather than overt acknowledgements.  Granted, SOE is ignoring or turning a blind eye to the &quot;auction&quot; sites even though it shut down the ones on eBay itself.  To their credit, with eBay, they had an official entity to whom they could go and demand auctions involving their property be disallowed.  With the private sites, they do not have that luxary.<br>
<br>
As for the proposal.  Sorry Robin, the sarcasm is lost unless one knows your stance on the practice of buying and selling and even then it falls on its face if one only takes into consideration the vocal protests of it being contra to the EULA.<br>
<br>
For me, I dislike the buying and selling of in-game items, plat, and characters for 2 reasons.  <br>
<br>
First and foremost it is intellectual property theft.  The only part of the EULA on buying and selling that I look at is the clause stating your acknowledgement SOE -owns- all in-game characters, items, and plat.  They are indentifying their IP ownership.  Do they own the idea of the character?  No.  Do they own the -form- of the character as it exists on their servers? Yes.  This is entirely analogous to the concept wherein you would own the story you write using Microsoft Word (wherein you purchase a license to use), but Microsoft retains ownership of the -form- in the .doc format (which can be changed without notice to anyone).  If you print it out on paper, you have purchased (not liscensed the use of) the supplies (paper, ink, printer) and thus own the -form- as well as the -substance- of your work.<br>
<br>
The second reason the buying and selling sickens me is the cheapening of any achievements for those playing -straight-.  If SOE were to sell (and buy) characters and stuff, what would be the point at all of doing anything in game as achievements for your character?  none whatsoever.  Right now, even with the sales sites, one can be assured he has achieved something within the rules while another has cheated his way their (some sense of accomplishment is still present).  If SOE sanctions selling by entering that market themselves, then all trace of that is removed and we might as well play <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.progressquest.com/">Progress Quest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> instead (or perhaps that really is what is being played by the macroists?)<br>
<br>
Influx of RL money into the game..... I wanted to play EQ to get away from RL.  To get away from the fact I am a female pushing 40 in a male dominated career field which often views those over 30 as &quot;washed up&quot; and &quot;fossils&quot; making the playing field entirely uneven against me.  To get away from the fact the playing field was never even in my own family with my brother being the &quot;golden child&quot; and I being the &quot;scape goat&quot;.  To get away from the constant irritation of working in a world where you have little to no &quot;control&quot; over your -own- destiny or path.  Etc, etc, etc.  I was wrong, EQ is not an escape, it is just another form of the same damn thing with a different veneer.<br>
<br>
I still play for the pockets I can find even as I know they are growing smaller. <p><center><table width="55%"><tr><td align="center">
